RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILLOWDALE STEEPLECHASE RACE 1 2 1/4M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 10000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A TIMBER OR HURDLE STAKES IN 2022-2023. To be ridden by apprentice riders. Weights will be determined based on the current ratings. The highest rated horse will be assigned 15 8 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including rider allowances. Riders who have never won a race, allowed 5 lbs. No other rider allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOOBY TRAP was settled back early on, advanced on the second circuit, then made a outside move on the far turn, then continued to close well and edged clear late to prove b est, driving. TOP BRASS (GB) pressed the early pace and made a bid to take over after a mile and drew clear, then was caught after the last jump and could not match strides with the winner, second best. FRONTLINE CITIZEN (IRE) was rated early, made a mild bid on the turn but flattened out, got nod for the show award. FAST VISION (FR) was settled back early, made a bid on the far turn but needed more late, missed show award. THREE O ONE set a pressured pace for the first mile, then stalked the pace and weakened in the lane. BALTIMORE KID (IRE) was reserved early and lacked a solid rally. LEFT BLANK was settled mid pack and tired.
